AGI -&nbsp;The name of Francis was the 15-month-old child who died after being killed by two pitbulls. The tregedia was consumed this morning in the locality Campolongo di Eboli, in Salernitano. According to a first reconstruction, the attack on the part of the two dogs took place inside the house, on the arrival of the health care of the 118 the little more than a year had already died.
&nbsp;
The child &nbsp;<b> was in arm to an uncle</b>, ready to go out of the house, when it was reached by dogs just outside the door. The two pitbulls hurled against the little boy and snatched him. The man remained unharmed, while the mother was injured in the attack. When he realized what was going on, &nbsp;<b> tried to save his son</b>, tearing him from the fury of the two dogs that turned against him.&nbsp; The woman was medicated on the spot by the health. In the two-storey villa, the reliefs and investigations of the Carabinieri of the Company of Eboli continue under the coordination of the Procura di Salerno. On the spot, pm and medical examiner.
&nbsp;
&nbsp; "A disgrace that softens the entire city", we read in a social post of the Municipality of Eboli. "Our community is deeply shaken by the immense tragedy that occurred this morning in Campolongo. The attack of two pitbulls has torn to life a child of just 15 months under the horrified eyes of the mother, also wounded. To the relatives of the little Francis we make our deep mourning simple, know that the words, in such cases, can hardly relieve the pain", is added in the post signed by the mayor and the municipal administration.
<div </div
<h2> &nbsp; The mayor: "Tragedy affecting all"</h2>
"This morning, around 8.15, there was the dog attack on the child who was held in his arms to his mother, they tell me. He literally ripped him out of his arms and snatched him." To say it is the mayor of Eboli (Salerno), Mario Conte, after being on the place where, this morning, the about a year old boy was killed and killed by one of the two dogs. "The veterinary service will take both dogs - adds the first citizen - which are not the property of the family affected by this tragedy, but of another family who lives in this house. It's a pitbull, I think it's a dog of this magnitude."
&nbsp;
"It was a fierce aggression - continues Conte - despite the fact that I believe that an uncle of the child has also intervened to try to free him and to tear him from the dog's jaws, but he did not succeed". "It all happened outside the house, on the patio that stands in front of the entrance balcony of the house and in very few moments and suddenly. They do not explain why this aggression, even because it is a dog that has always been there," says the mayor, according to whom what happened "must be a warning to those who own these dogs who are unfortunately particular. They tell me that if they are not treated in a certain way and if they neglect etc., they can then have these sudden attitudes of aggression. So you have to make sure that those who have these dogs are very careful." "It is a tragedy that strikes everyone," says Count.&nbsp;
<h2> There is no list of dangerous dogs
There is no list of potentially "problematic" dogs in Italy. In 2006, the Ministry of Health issued an order on the protection of public safety from dog aggression, in which a list of breeds considered dangerous was planned. "Successive ordinances have abolished this list - says lawyer&nbsp;<b>Claudia Taccani, head of the law office of Oipa</b>, the international organization for the protection of animals - because of its uncertainty and, above all, the discrimination of races".
&nbsp;

